In order to move the (processed results of) `SELL_TO` to the `CustomerData` element, you must do two things:

 1. Point your `xsl:apply-templates` instruction to the correct path to the node -
    i.e. change:
    
        &lt;CustomerData&gt;
            &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;SELL_TO&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/CustomerData&gt;
    
    to:
    
        &lt;CustomerData&gt;
            &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;../SELL_TO&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/CustomerData&gt;
 2. Remove the `SELL_TO` element from the default processing order by
    adding the following template:
        
        &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;ORDER&quot;&gt;
            &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;ORDER_DATA&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/xsl:template&gt;

       Otherwise it will be processed twice. 
    
    Alternatively, change the instruction:
    
        &lt;xsl:apply-templates/&gt;
    
    in your main template to:
    
        &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;ORDER_LIST/ORDER/ORDER_DATA&quot;/&gt;

