We&#39;re using a React + Webpack setup. The traditional way to import libraries and components is something like:
```
import React from &#39;react&#39;
import styled from &#39;styled-components&#39;
import Button from &#39;../components/Button&#39;
```

My idea is about putting all packages and components into one file. Something like this:

`/common/index.js:`
```
import React from &#39;react&#39;
import styled from &#39;styled-components&#39;
import Button from &#39;../components/Button&#39;

export {React,styled,Button}
```

Then in other files, I can just do

```
import {React,styled,Button} from &#39;../common&#39;
```

I&#39;ve been using this pattern on the server for the past few weeks. It makes importing faster (typing wise). It also gets rid of the problem that files have 10 or so imports (especially in frontend) and imports take a large part of the screen (the most valuable part of the screen...)

